1.title: Sex
1.plot: It's time to share our carnal knowledge. We get down and dirty with what's on every man's mind, every 15 seconds a day ... sex.

2.title: Double Standards
2.plot: Some double standards put women on a pedestal while others put men on a higher pay scale. Double standards can be completely unfair or agreed upon by both genders. Most are archaic and have no place in modern society but have lasted the test of time. Our guys take on the most unsettling, the most debatable, and the most troubling of the double standards.

3.title: Communication
3.plot:

4.title: Cheating
4.plot: Cheating has derailed more relationships than any other definable act. Is being a monogamous partner not included in a man's genetic code? Once the circle of trust has been broken, can a relationship be salvaged or will the sins of the past be revisited on the next unwitting partner?

5.title: Baggage
5.plot: Have you ever arrived on the first date with all of your past relationship baggage packed? Do you have so much that it's piled up all around you and acts like a wall that keeps everyone who has ever tried to get close to you far, far away? Do you think men have more baggage or are women the "over-packers?"

6.title: Insecurities
6.plot: What worries guys and girls the most? What gets you jealous? Do money issues make you more insecure? Did you find something suspicious on his cell phone? We will unlock the dark secrets of our collective psyches.

imdb.plot outline: Countless books, articles, movies and visits to therapists have all been devoted to one concept: the way the male brain processes in regards to the way the female brain processes the same information. Thus we have embraced the popular concept, "Women Are From Venus, Men Are From Mars." Women have been fed a steady diet catered by magazine editors from Cosmopolitan and Glamour, amongst others, touting what men "truly believe" about the fairer sex. We can debate the merits of this endless stream of Pablum ad nauseam but the gender difference will become glaringly apparent when a "safe space" is present and men can openly speak their minds without fear of repercussion. Each episode will showcase trending and controversial topics that will then be dissected and explored by our comedic hosts, and an all male panel of fellow comics. The lively, comedic debates will provide our viewers with insight into what truly goes on inside a man's head, despite what women think they know or believe. During each episode, one of our comics will interview women on the street and bring the clips back to our panel to discuss.
